<paragraph id="8BB6368C924C772EFF43F936FA15BB03" blockId="28.[136,1452,1586,2080]" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924C772EFF43F936FE2BBB4B" bold="true" box="[189,442,1766,1792]" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924C772EFE44F937FE42BB4B" box="[442,467,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">—</emphasis>
The species has been collected several times in only one locality in the municipality of Camacan, in the “Reserva Particular do Patrimônio Natural Serra Bonita”. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F924C772EFC2EF8DAFB27BB6F" box="[976,1206,1802,1828]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitoriana">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924C772EFC2EF8DAFB27BB6F" box="[976,1206,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">Bertolonia vitoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an EOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B69924C772EFA94F8DAFA32BB6C" box="[1386,1443,1802,1831]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" unit="km" value="3.0">3 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B69924C772EFEE6F8FEFEC2BB00" box="[280,339,1838,1867]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" unit="km" value="1.0">1 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Critically Endangered” (CR), following 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D924C772EFB90F8FEFA95BB03" author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[1134,1284,1838,1864]" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3136507924C772EFF43F882FF73B46B" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB6368C924C772EFF43F882FF73B46B" blockId="28.[136,1452,1586,2080]" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924C772EFF43F882FE98BB27" bold="true" box="[189,265,1874,1900]" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F924C772EFED8F882FD80BB27" box="[294,529,1874,1900]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitoriana">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924C772EFED8F882FD80BB27" box="[294,529,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">Bertolonia vitoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E924C772EFD35F882FC9EBB27" box="[715,783,1874,1900]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane rainforests (
<figureCitation id="13322A09924C772EFB4AF882FA8ABB27" box="[1204,1307,1874,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[136,229,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[346,1239,435,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-140@19.[340,1247,425,1706]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A.Bertolonia linearifolia. B. Bertolonia maculata. C. Bertolonia marmorata. D. Bertolonia reginatoi. E. Bertolonia riocontensis. F. Bertolonia violacea. G. Bertolonia vitoriana." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597718/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CF19B69924C772EFB10F882FA8ABB27" box="[1262,1307,1874,1900]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.3" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" unit="g" value="13.0">13g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
), on shaded and moist slopes. Collected with flowers from November to January, and fruits from November to April and June. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F924C772EFF76F84AFEFCBBFF" box="[136,365,1946,1972]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitoriana">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924C772EFF76F84AFEFCBBFF" box="[136,365,1946,1972]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">Bertolonia vitoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the stem, petioles, leaf blades and hypanthium only glandulose-punctate, leaves with flat surfaces and the suprabasal inner pair of veins, and flowers with white petals and yellow anthers. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F924C772EFF76F832FEFFBBB7" box="[136,366,2018,2044]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitoriana">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924C772EFF76F832FEFFBBB7" box="[136,366,2018,2044]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">Bertolonia vitoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F924C772EFDFEF833FDFFBBB7" box="[512,622,2018,2044]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924C772EFDFEF833FDFFBBB7" box="[512,622,2018,2044]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">B. bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. For more details see the notes under 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F924C772EFBE7F833FB16BBB7" box="[1049,1159,2018,2044]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924C772EFBE7F833FB16BBB7" box="[1049,1159,2018,2044]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">B. bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D924C772EFB55F832FAEDBBB7" author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[1195,1404,2018,2045]" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" pagination="767 - 792" refId="ref18533" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2018) Increased Sampling in Under-Collected Areas Sheds New Light on the Diversity and Distribution of Bertolonia, an Atlantic Forest Endemic Genus. Systematic Botany 43 (3): 767 - 792. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 697490" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bacci 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E924C772EFB0CF833FAB2BBB7" box="[1266,1315,2018,2044]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="181">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation id="C68B0337924C772EFF76F7D6FF4DB46B" box="[136,220,2054,2080]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2" pageId="28" pageNumber="181" tableUuid="DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
